30/01/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The operational command of the BiH Armed Forces was transferred on Monday (January 29th) to Camp Butmir, near Sarajevo, where EUFOR headquarters is currently located.
Addressing the formal ceremony, the NATO HQ Commander in BiH, General Richard Wightman, said the transfer represents a first step towards the eventual handover of the Camp's command to the BiH military.
Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic also praised the transfer, crediting the reform processes in the defence sector.
(PBS BiH, RTRS - 29/01/07)
